    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1914-04-21T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1914-04-21T00:00:00-05:00" n="714"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d714">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 812.00/11677.</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Mexican Chargé d’Affaires</gloss> to
                        the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#left">No. 134.]</seg>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Mexican Embassy</hi>, <lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1914-04-21">
                            <hi rend="italic">April 21, 1914</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Excellency</hi>: At half past nine to-day I had the honor
                    to receive from His Excellency the Provisional Constitutional President of the
                    United Mexican States, General Victoriano Huerta, a telegram as follows: <quote
                        rend="blockquote">
                        <p>We are fighting at Vera Cruz against the unlawful landing of American
                            marines.</p>
                        <p>In the name of the Government that you represent, bring this fact to the
                            attention of whom it may concern.</p>
                        <p>Acknowledge receipt of this cable.</p>
                    </quote>
                </p>
                <p>In bringing the foregoing to the attention of your excellency I renew [etc.]</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">A. Algara E. de Terreros</hi>
                    </signed>.</closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
